<h3 style="color: #111; font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold; margin: 0 0 15px">INBOX ZERO</h3>            <div>
<p>One thing you can be sure of during the holidays is that you're going to get some bad email. We hate bad email, so we put together this list of tools to help you bulk unsubscribe from stuff you don't want.</p>
<p><a href="http://blog.getvero.com/how-to-unsubscribe/?vero_conv=368317933&amp;vero_id=test2%40getvero.com" style="color: #2BA6CB; text-decoration: none"><strong>How to Unsubscribe From Unwanted Email</strong></a></p>
<p>That might seem strange coming from an email marketing business, but we truly want to help people send better emails, not just more emails. I hope you find it useful.</p>
<p>Cheers,</p>
<p>Chris (<a href="https://twitter.com/chexton?vero_conv=368317933&amp;vero_id=test2%40getvero.com" text="" alt="" target="_blank" rel="nofollow" style="color: #2BA6CB; text-decoration: none">@chexton</a>)</p>
<p>PS - Jimmy wrote a piece for <i>Marketing Land</i> on what types of emails to send during the holidays. <a href="http://marketingland.com/thinking-outside-box-4-emails-sending-holiday-season-109386?vero_conv=368317933&amp;vero_id=test2%40getvero.com" text="" alt="" target="_blank" rel="nofollow" title="Link: http://marketingland.com/thinking-outside-box-4-emails-sending-holiday-season-109386" style="color: #2BA6CB; text-decoration: none">Check it out here.</a></p>
